docs.abstract: In India, start-ups are opening a new front in the global ride-hailing battles, just as Uber prepares to go public.
docs.snippet: In India, start-ups are opening a new front in the global ride-hailing battles, just as Uber prepares to go public.
docs.lead_paragraph: BANGALORE, India — In Uber’s vision of the future, self-driving cars will whisk us everywhere, eliminating the need for its millions of human drivers.

headline.main: Ride-Sharing’s Future? It May Sit on Electric Motorbikes
headline.print_headline: How Scooters Are Shaking Up Ride Sharing

docs.abstract: Three women near Minneapolis argue that Amazon retaliated against them after they protested their working conditions.
docs.snippet: Three women near Minneapolis argue that Amazon retaliated against them after they protested their working conditions.
docs.lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — Three Somali women working for Amazon near Minneapolis have accused the company of creating a hostile environment for Muslim workers and of retaliating against them for protesting their work conditions, according to a filing submitted this week to federal regulators.

headline.main: 3 Muslim Workers at Amazon File Federal Discrimination Complaint

docs.abstract: The insurer was the first of four victims linked to the pair, in what the authorities say was an aggressive hacking campaign.
docs.snippet: The insurer was the first of four victims linked to the pair, in what the authorities say was an aggressive hacking campaign.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — The Justice Department unsealed an indictment of two Chinese nationals on Thursday, charging them with the 2014 hack of the insurance company Anthem and attacks on three other, unnamed American businesses the next year.

headline.main: Two From China Are Charged in 2014 Anthem Data Breach

docs.abstract: The chief executive of the lingerie brand’s parent company said that it “must evolve and change to grow.” The annual special has aired on network TV since 2001.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Victoria’s Secret fashion show, an annual spectacle of glitter, cleavage and pop music, will no longer air on network television after a nearly two-decade run.

headline.print_headline: Alibaba’s Fortunes Dim in Shadow of Trade War

docs.abstract: Brian Hofer, a paralegal who drafted the ordinance, is pushing for anti-surveillance measures across California. He has already gotten more than two dozen approved.
docs.snippet: Brian Hofer, a paralegal who drafted the ordinance, is pushing for anti-surveillance measures across California. He has already gotten more than two dozen approved.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — As San Francisco’s Board of Supervisors prepared to vote Tuesday on an ordinance forbidding city agencies to use facial recognition technology, some proponents of the measure were uncertain if they had the necessary support. Two of the legislators who were for it had called in sick.

headline.main: The Man Behind San Francisco’s Facial Recognition Ban Is Working on More. Way More.

docs.abstract: The move will help end a yearlong standoff that has heightened North American tensions but does not guarantee passage of a new trade deal.
docs.snippet: The move will help end a yearlong standoff that has heightened North American tensions but does not guarantee passage of a new trade deal.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration reached an agreement with Canada and Mexico to lift tariffs on metal imports, resolving a yearlong standoff that inflamed North Atlantic tensions and complicated efforts to ratify a revised trade deal.

headline.main: United States Reaches Deal to Lift Metal Tariffs on Canada and Mexico

docs.abstract: A possible merger with Viacom is back in play for the most-watched network, after it was affected by claims of misconduct at its executive wing, news division and prime-time shows.
docs.snippet: A possible merger with Viacom is back in play for the most-watched network, after it was affected by claims of misconduct at its executive wing, news division and prime-time shows.
docs.lead_paragraph: CBS will finish the 2018-19 season as the most-watched broadcast network for the 11th year in a row, a fact that executives did not neglect to mention from the Carnegie Hall stage at their annual pitch to advertisers on Wednesday.

headline.main: CBS Unveils Its New Lineup After a Season of Crisis

docs.abstract: The deal is the card giant’s latest effort to expand into the hospitality industry, giving it the country’s biggest privately held option for reserving tables.
docs.snippet: The deal is the card giant’s latest effort to expand into the hospitality industry, giving it the country’s biggest privately held option for reserving tables.
docs.lead_paragraph: American Express has considered dining perks one of the main benefits for its card members, helping them book tables at hot spots and offering them rewards points for doing so. Now it is taking a new step into the industry — by buying the country’s biggest privately held restaurant reservation service.

headline.main: American Express to Buy Resy, a Restaurant Booking Service

byline.original: By Michael J. de la Merced
